Here's a minimal API endpoint that accepts multiple image files plus a text description via `multipart/form-data`:

```csharp
// In Program.cs

var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

// Raise the max request body size (default is ~30MB)
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o => o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 50 * 1024 * 1024);

var app = builder.Build();

app.MapPost("/upload", async (
    [FromForm] IFormFileCollection files,
    [FromForm] string description,
    CancellationToken ct) =>
{
    if (files.Count == 0)
        return Results.BadRequest("No files uploaded.");

    var allowed = new[] { "image/jpeg", "image/png", "image/gif", "image/webp" };
    var saved = new List<string>();

    foreach (var file in files)
    {
        if (!allowed.Contains(file.ContentType, StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase))
            return Results.BadRequest($"'{file.FileName}' is not a supported image type.");

        var path = Path.Combine("uploads", $"{Guid.NewGuid()}{Path.GetExtension(file.FileName)}");
        Directory.CreateDirectory("uploads");

        await using var stream = File.Create(path);
        await file.CopyToAsync(stream, ct);
        saved.Add(path);
    }

    return Results.Ok(new { Description = description, FileCount = saved.Count, Paths = saved });
})
.DisableAntiforgery()          // required for form binding without antiforgery tokens
.Accepts<IFormFileCollection>("multipart/form-data");

app.Run();
```

**Key points:**

- **`[FromForm]`** — binds each parameter from the multipart form. `IFormFileCollection` grabs all file parts; `string description` grabs the text field.
- **`ConfigureKestrel`** — raises the request body limit to 50 MB. Without this, large uploads get a `413`.
- **`.DisableAntiforgery()`** — needed in .NET 8+ because form binding now enforces antiforgery by default.
- Content-type validation prevents non-image uploads.

**Example `curl` call:**

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/upload \
  -F "files=@photo1.jpg" \
  -F "files=@photo2.png" \
  -F "description=Vacation photos"
```
